RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 55. Maiden Special Weight Purse 24000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LAPUSH moved up along the inside to take the lead before going a quarter mile, saved ground setting the pace and drew off to win as much the best. COASTAL GIRL was prominent from the start while racing three-wide and finished well for second in a good effort. SHELBY SHORTSTOP raced four-wide while being forwardly placed and picked up the show in a steady effort. DREWY bobbled at the start, then moved up between horses to prompt the issue to the stretch and tired. CHIRISCA was unhurried early, came three-wide into the stretch but failed to seriously threaten. TRES VITE was close up early while saving ground but gave way after three furlongs.

ENTRY.NAME: Lapush
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, saved ground, much the best

ENTRY.NAME: Tres Vite
ENTRY.COMMENT: close up early, saved ground, gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Coastal Girl
ENTRY.OWNER: Hagen Ron Hagen Nina and Sample Frank T

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WESTERBERG stalked the pace while racing three-wide, angled out four-wide nearing the quarter pole and finished strongly to be up in the final sixteenth. START THEM UP hopped slightly at the start then saved ground while being allowed to settle, moved through along the inside to take the lead nearing the three-eighths pole, opened a clear lead entering the stretch but was unable to resist the winner late. NIGHT TO REMEMBER set the pace for nearly five furlongs while racing removed from the rail, responded briefly when headed to dispute the issue to the stretch and tired during the drive. PER THE HORSE RACING INTEGRITY AND WELFARE UNIT, NIGHT TO REMEMBER HAS BEE DQ'D FOR A POSITIVE TEST.

ENTRY.NAME: Start Them Up
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped start, settled, saved ground, led 3/8, clear, caught late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 13500. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GLIMPSE OF GOLD saved ground stalking the pace, angled out two-wide leaving the three-sixteenths pole and finished strongly to wear down SANDY HARBOR in the final seventy yards. SANDY HARBOR saved ground setting the pressured pace, opened a clear lead entering the stretch but was unable to resist the winner late. SECRET HOTTIE prompted the pace while racing three-wide to the stretch and weakened. A FRIEND INDEED dropped back early, came five-wide into the stretch but failed to seriously threaten. DREAMINGOFBLING gave way after showing brief speed from between horses. PER RULING FROM HORSE RACING INTEGRITY AND WELFARE UNIT, GLIMPSE OF GOLD HAS BEEN DQ'D FOR A POSITIVE TEST.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIST OONA B stalked the pace while racing two-wide, came three-wide into the stretch and finished strongly to be up in the final sixteenth to win going away. TENNESSEE MOON vied with AWESOME DAZE for the lead from along the inside, responded when asked to open a clear lead entering the stretch, could not resist the winner but held on gamely during the drive. AWESOME DAZE vied for the lead from along the outside to the stretch and weakened during the drive. BIKINI NATION was allowed to settle in stride, came four-wide into the stretch and went evenly late. TED'S CANDY GIRL dropped back early, swung out to be three-wide entering the stretch and failed to seriously threaten. G G RULES saved ground while racing in the middle of the field but lacked a rally when asked.

ENTRY.NAME: G G Rules
ENTRY.COMMENT: mid pack, saved ground, lacked rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DYF saved ground stalking the pace, angled out four-wide nearing the quarter pole to launch his bid, took the lead leaving the eighth pole and then was all out to hold off TWO PRINCES late. TWO PRINCES was forwardly placed while racing three-wide, dropped back slightly on the turn then came five-wide into the stretch and finished fast to just miss. IDIDNTSEETHATCOMIN saved ground setting the pace into the stretch and held on well for third when headed. SILENT DECLARATION disputed the pace to the stretch while racing three-wide and finished fairly well in a steady effort. UNION BLISS vied for the lead from between horses for a half mile and tired. STREET DEMAND was unhurried early, came three-wide into the stretch and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Dyf
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, saved ground, 4-wide 1/4, led leaving 1/8, all out

ENTRY.NAME: Ididntseethatcomin
ENTRY.OWNER: Friendship Stable Molloy Kandie and Fredrickson Craig

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SAILING IN saved ground setting the pace and drew clear during the drive to win with something left. GOIN' COASTAL was close up early while racing between horses, came three-wide into the stretch and finished in a mild rally. BABY MARTINI was unhurried early, came two-wide into the stretch and improved her position late. FOREVER AMBER dropped back early while saving ground, came three-wide into the stretch but was unable to seriously threaten. NOW SAY SO saved ground while being allowed to settle and tired during the late stages. PISTA GIRL was reserved off the early pace while racing three-wide, came five-wide into the stretch and gave way.
